column5: We are looking at going here next year. Can anybody share any information about Lac Seul Outposts? Accomadations, boats, fishing etc. Thanks Charlie
great fishing, nice people, camp manager likes coors light

I have made over two dozen trips to Ojibway and can attest to the fact that it is a top notch outfit. Great cabins, remote location, only lodge for 30 miles other than occasional outpost cabin. Located in the heart of great fishing. Word of advice, follow the rules as camp owner tolerates no crap, however is fair.
DON'T BE CARVING UP THE BIG FISH, THERES PLENTY OF EATERS.
i will be in trouble. All I catch is big fish!!!!!!
